				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, the reason I'm using MP3 is I'm intending to distribute this in a technically legal manner.  So I'd include the emulator, and I suppose the ROM patch (which is actually a pretty good idea), but it would be up to the end user to supply the MP3s and the ROM...and I'm pretty confident the end user will have the songs in an MP3 format (since that's how they were originally distributed).
<br />
<br />Basically, if I use OGG or WAV, then I need to include a song pack, or require the end user to convert their MP3's, which would be an annoyance.
<br />
<br />Oh, and I got the MP3 files legally from the band (The Megas, <!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.themegas.com">www.themegas.com</a><!-- w -->) when I bought the CD.
<br />
<br />Anyway, I found a RAM map for MM2:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://datacrystal.org/wiki/Mega_Man_2:RAM_map">http://datacrystal.org/wiki/Mega_Man_2:RAM_map</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />So, if I'm reading this correctly, the current song playing is stored in $0067 in the RAM, right?  That'd make it pretty simple.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

